Date of Birth: July 16, 1781<br/>
Birthplace: Derryfield, New Hampshire, USA<br/>
Death: May 23, 1854<br/>
<br/>
Born July 16, 1781, at Derryfield, Hillsboro Co., New Hampshire, to Asael Smith and Mary Duty.
Ordained high priest June 3, 1833, by Lyman Wight;
sustained as assistant counselor to the First Presidency Sept 3, 1837, at age 56;
released at the death of Joseph Smith June 27,1844; ordained Patriarch to the Church Jan. 1, 1849, at age 67;
died May 23, 1854, at Salt Lake City, Salt Lake Co., Utah, at age 72.